      <a href="https://orangette.net/2010/08/but-then/#comment-21855"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2010-08-30T02:48:49-04:00">Monday, August 30, 2010 at 2:48 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I made the cobbler last night with 16 oz. bag of frozen mixed berries from Trader Joe&#39;s that I had in the freezer and baked it in a 10-inch glass pie dish. It was delicious &#8211; just sweet enough to bring out the berry flovors. The dough transformed into flaky and tender biscuits.  As you said, it was still delicious the next day for breakfast.</p>
    </div>

